The President of the United States, Joseph R. Biden Jr., has issued an Executive Order declaring a national emergency with regards to hostage-taking and wrongful detention of U.S. nationals. This action has been taken under the International Emergency Economic Powers Act. The President highlights that hostage-taking and wrongful detention are serious acts that undermine the rule of law. These actions, carried out by terrorist organizations, criminal groups, and other malicious actors, pose a threat to the international political system, the safety of U.S. nationals, and people abroad. The President believes that the wrongful detention and hostage-taking of U.S. nationals abroad present an unusual and extraordinary threat to the national security, foreign policy, and economy of the United States. The Executive Order is enclosed with the report.